  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Celebrating Applet Success**\n\nI\'m thrilled to report that both `lint_applet` and `compile_applet` are executing perfectly! The applet\'s conceptual framework and design choices are now ready for a concise summary. I am excited to communicate these details in the style you requested.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully completed and compiled the **Dzair Craft** prototype application\342\200\224a high-fidelity MVP e-commerce marketplace centered on Algerian traditional garments, jewelry, and artisan crafts. It is fully built using React with local persistence storage (`localStorage`), specifically structured to serve as a reliable blueprint for your Figma UI/UX designs and stakeholder presentation next week.\n\nHere is a conceptual and functional overview of what has been implemented:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual Identity & Aesthetic Choices\n- **Warm Sand Palette**: Framed by a clean, high-contrast layout utilizing generous negative space, soft off-whites, and deep stone slate colors inspired by the Sahara desert.\n- **Traditional Color Accents**: Accented by rich amber-golds representing traditional Algerian jewelry and deep emerald-greens reflective of classical Moorish architecture and textiles.\n- **Pairing Elegance**: Integrated **Playfair Display** (a sophisticated editorial serif) for headings and cultural titles, paired with **Inter** (a highly legible sans-serif) for functional UI elements.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\233\241\357\270\217 Functional Modules Built\n\n1. **The Heritage Catalog**\n   - **Cultural Artifacts Feed**: Showcases 8 authentic Algerian items representing historical centers of craftsmanship (e.g., Algiers, Tlemcen, Kabylie, Ghardaia, Constantine). Items range from UNESCO-heritage bridal dress layouts to naturally dyed organic wool rugs.\n   - **Dual Fulfillments Modes**: Integrated interactive toggle ribbons on cards and detail modals to separate elements available exclusively for direct **Purchase** (e.g., copper teasets, ceramics) vs garments available also for **Temporary Rental** (e.g., Karakou velvet jackets).\n   - **Refined Filtering**: Allows searching by keyword and filtering dynamically by category group, geographical artisan origin region, and maximum budget slider.\n   - **Atelier Inspection Drawers**: Clickable mock detail overlays revealing materials, available sizing, stock counts, and background context for local guilds.\n\n2. **Algerian Interbank Payment Gateway Simulator**\n   - **SATIM Secure Tunneling**: Mimics the exact secure payment structures utilized in Algeria with support for **CIB cards** (SATIM Interbank connection), **EDAHABIA cards** (Alg\303\251rie Poste Baridimob connection), and international cards.\n   - **Dynamic Card Visualizer**: Features a visual debit card template that instantly remodels its color theme, bank labels, and layout depending on the selected card type.\n   - **Rental Range Selector**: Enables buyers renting garments to specify delivery dates and select hire periods ranging from 3 to 14 days, dynamically scaling subtotal estimates.\n\n3. **Vendor Administration Portal (Seller Dashboard)**\n   - **Guild Business Statistics (KPIs)**: Measures gross virtual earnings, pending processing shipments, and active garments on rent to illustrate business health to stakeholders.\n   - **Inventory Record Manager**: Displays a quick-access table of registered items, permitting seller coordinators to easily adjust stock counts or completely de-list products.\n   - **Incoming Client Orders (Fulfillment Process)**: Details customer shipping addresses, phone numbers, and payment details. Includes an order-status tracker reflecting Yalidine EMS courier progress (from *Pending Review* to *Processing & Packaged*, *On Transit*, and *Delivered/Completed*).\n   - **Listing Submission Form**: Allows instant addition of new custom handicrafts, seamlessly injecting them into the buyer\'s shop loop with local persistence.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\232\200 Interactive Test Walkthrough for Your Stakeholder Meeting\nTo highlight the responsive flow during your presentation, you can perform this clean live loop in the preview frame:\n1. **Explore the Shop**: Browse the catalog, filter by the \"Kabylie\" or \"Algiers\" regions, and click **Explore Artifact** to open a piece.\n2. **Add to Cart**: Click **Rent Dress** on a garment and **Buy Item** on a handicraft.\n3. **Checkout Selection**: Open the cart drawer, click **Proceed to Payment**, fill in mock Algiers shipping details, select **EDAHABIA Card**, enter any mock credentials, and click **Authorize**.\n4. **Inspect Fulfillment**: Once the secure SATIM loader finishes and confirmed order results display, click **Go to Seller Orders Page**. Switch tabs in the portal to look at your fresh incoming order, update its courier delivery state to *On Transit*, and inspect how the global gross earnings instantly recalculated!\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 974942321
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
